hi: Can you explain the leave with wages policy in mines?
Yes:
Every person employed in a mine who has completed a calendar year service therein shall be allowed, during the subsequent calendar year, leave with wages calculated:
· in the case of a person employed below ground at the rate of 1 day for every 15 days of work performed by him,
· in any other case, at the rate of 1 day for every 20 days of work performed by him/her.
The owner, agent, or manager of every mine shall maintain, in respect of every employee thereof, a record of leave with wages in Form G and H.
